{
  "stem": "9.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think they went all the way to the border at that point.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They also-- the Germans had an idea they want to get rid of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For absolutely no other reason-- but they pick the Jews, the gypsies, the handicapped, the psychologically ill, as their scapegoats.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hitler wanted to get elected in 1933, and he didn't know how to do it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He knew that many people were afraid of the communism.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he decided to make-- promise the people that he's going to make a clean, German-blooded race.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And anyone that had any mixed blood, even three, four generations back, was not pure blood.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's why he started searching out everybody that was 1/2 Jewish, 1/4 Jewish, intermarried, maybe great grandparents somewhere were intermarried.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was enough to eliminate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But in the beginning-- I have learned that after the war-- Hitler did not want to kill Jews, or gypsies, or all these people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He wanted to get rid of them, but no country in the world wanted to accept them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's why-- anybody realizes it-- for us, Israel is so, so important.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because we feel if we had a country, we could run somewhere.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But if we did not have a country, we couldn't do anything about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So even we don't live there or anything like that-- but as long as we have a voice somewhere.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In case of some problems, we have a place to go to-- in case of emergency.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Germans started to get-- oh, I think this is where we were at that point.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I remember once an incident when the SS men came along, and I found myself somewhere in a workshop.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I finally saw a shelf above me.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
